ntent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEfq2i8Y76VfpqDgaGvfjW-jyRe9d0j455-oN2lonRk35O8FqfFVbYq_wYboTKQNiNLAU4ovqiJgJCqULerkeDQK7kBSSxsaVa3L3zabZsqDZSExCGFWtPJr5Gqk0qSvUTMUS-PXA=w224-h298-k-no-pi-20-ya320-ro-0-fo100"}]'::jsonb, '{"Friday": ["5:30 a.m.–10 p.m."], "Monday": ["5:30 a.m.–10 p.m."], "Saturday": ["5:30 a.m.–10 p.m."], "Sunday": ["5:30 a.m.–10 p.m."], "Thursday": ["5:30 a.m.–10 p.m."], "Tuesday": ["5:30 a.m.–10 p.m."], "Wednesday": ["5:30 a.m.–10 p.m."]}'::jsonb, '[{"Name": "Michał", "ProfilePicture": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW260yp8NAWUwCD-Zo-78UhjO_cYO9krHq3RHn7i22WSJ7NlPI5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100", "Rating": 1, "Description": "I’ll start off by saying the courts are very nice. Unfortunately when you pull up to this business to park you will see two dogs in cages to your left. We asked the parking worker about them and their situation. He said that they have been in there for a year and don’t get out. They used to be ran when there was a soccer field in the back, but not anymore and that they belong to the owner of the pickleball courts.\nWe walked into the courts and talked to the main guy you pay before playing about the two dogs. He didn’t want to talk about it and wouldn’t even look us in the eyes. We asked if we could walk the dogs? No. We asked if he thinks we could buy the dogs to find them better homes(this is my work here in Vietnam) he said no. We asked for the pickleball court owners contact info so we could talk to them….No.\nAfter our session I went over to see the dogs. They bark, but do not bite and are clearly begging to be let out. I stayed with them for a few minutes then had to go back inside of the pickleball court to wash my hands as the dogs were covered in their own shit and piss. No soap in the men’s bathroom by the way. When I came back out another man came out and started telling us it’s his two dogs and he runs them.\nUnfortunately, we feel his story of taking care of these dogs didn’t sound right. I asked if his dogs were ran/walked why are they covered in shit and piss? To this there was no response. A lady came out a few mins later and started spraying the dogs down with water. The man who said the dogs were his also took the hose a few mins later. We offered to buy the dogs off him if he was the in fact the owner and that we will find them new homes and give them a good life. We got a “No”\nSo the dogs belong to the owner of the courts or the guy who came out and said the dogs were his? We don’t know the true story.\nAll we ask is for the owners to reach out to us through this review and have a chat about these dogs and how we can better their lives.\nWe will no longer be supporting this business and giving them any of our money. There are too many other pickleball courts around the city to choose from.\nIf you care about animals and their welfare I would hope you stay away as well.\nI hope I hear from the owners and we can work something out so no one will have to see this when coming in for their games and most importantly for these two poor dogs to get proper homes and the love they deserve.", "Images": ["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0XUvsj4ZRAU6cSa6yOpGUA9ZgMrUdoHQmP6_qmyWuTCl3r98WzV2t7uCShsxtvTVcm43sHFmc9arqayTPtxU_XQ3p3XeiQztogAnFrpwjaQdMpYVyJUztsVkOwA8wtqFRxIommXcGBzeVF=k-no"], "When": "2025-12-26"}, {"Name": "Sebas Paz", "ProfilePicture": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUYnCB63f0J0e9SwoJopyY7v2TlDjCQMOwRSaoHRDsGeGTHLlq1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100", "Rating": 5, "Description": "Great futsal court, the grass is good quality and in great shape.", "Images": ["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1rTz3k6ibHkOWWlApinutzj5xCG2yUBsaY-QyR3HCDp3rdlBec3dYOSiNNc-f5gmWyIQusydC7jwVAS8ELTbKNrAwPkduWUgbWwPxFtP3jSrEAEdqi9afzb2Z-aDMM4MJZb2M1AA=k-no", "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0pMADpuNmOnfHnPRassylvFMNA7b4scvssofl-oFUFt5HVho7_pssGWKLb42ggScyjLrqgd98obND0-7FQ-KYeDNn5-ryUKzEJEUoEIRH-3mlsxYAblO_jjJCN5Ml4LVpjWoHk=k-no"], "When": "2024-3